conversations_v0.question: For an assignment, Preston looked at which countries got the most Nobel Prizes in various decades. In the 1980s, how many more Nobel Prize winners did Germany have than Japan?
conversations_v0.answer:
Find the 1980 s column. Find the numbers in this column for Germany and Japan.

Germany: 11
Japan: 2

Now subtract:

11 − 2 = 9

Germany had 9 more Nobel Prize winners in the 1980 s than Japan.
